#Normalized Avg LOS by Type of Service
d1<- df %>% 
  group_by(service) %>% 
  summarize(avg_los = mean(los, na.rm=TRUE)) 

d1 <- na.omit(d1)

d1$los_z= round((d1$avg_los - mean(d1$avg_los))/sd(d1$avg_los),2)
d1$los_type = ifelse(d1$los_z<0, "below","above")
ggplot(d1,aes(x=reorder(service, los_z), y=los_z, label=los_z)) + 
  geom_bar(stat='identity', aes(fill=los_type), width=.5) + scale_fill_manual(name="LOS",
          labels = c("Above Average", "Below Average"),
          values= c("above"="#00ba38", "below"="#f8766d")) + labs(subtitle= "Normalized Average LOS by type of Service",
       title= "Normalized Average Analysis") +
  coord_flip()

library(dplyr)
 avg_los <- (mean(df$los) + sd(df$los))


df = df %>% 
  mutate(los_flag = case_when(
    los < avg_los ~ "0",
    los > avg_los ~ "1"))
# 0 means it is below the avg, 1 means it is above average
df$target <- df$los_flag
library(tidyverse) 
# input variables

m1 <- df %>%
